cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with community detection in social networks, which is a fundamental problem in social network analysis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a recursive algorithm for enumerating all maximal $\Delta$-k-plexes in temporal graphs. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the practical feasibility of the proposed approach and presents experimental results on real-world social networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are less likely as they are not directly related to the topic of the paper.
